title: MSC #4, Chile Challenge
description: MSC #4, Chile Challenge is a part of the Mountain States Cup (MSC)--the largest full-discipline (endurance and gravity) race series in the United States. Cross country and four cross on Saturday. Short track, super d and downhill on Sunday. Test your skills on the infamous World Cup courses at Angel Fire Resort.
course: For all course maps and descriptions, visit http://www.racemsc.com.
registration: The best way to register for Chile Challenge is online at www.active.com! Online registration deadline is Wednesday, June 1 at 11:59 p.m. There is no fee this year for registering online at Active.com. You can also download the Chile Challenge Registration Form from http://www.racemsc.com.
directions:
Angel Fire is located in New Mexico, not too far from its border with Colorado.

If you are headed from Denver or anywhere else in Colorado, make your way to I-25 South towards Colorado Springs. Take ext 446 US-64 W towards Taos. Stay on US-64W for 68.2 miles. Then turn left on NM-434/Mountain View Blvd. for a few miles and you\'re there!

title: Angel Fire's Oso High Mountain Bike Race
South Enchanted Loop Gran Fondo Test Ride
description: Come join the Bike N Sport Racing team for one of New Mexico\'s best road rides, the 104 mile Southern Enchanted loop!  This is a test ride for a possible Gran Fondo next year and a fundraiser for the Bike N Sport Racing team.  We will have limited support. Please bring your own tools/tubes and plenty of food and water.  There are two towns on the route at about 20 miles (Angel Fire) and 60 miles (Mora), but bring money!
course:
The link below has a great description of this loop; we will ride it clockwise instead of counter-clockwise.  Expect ride time to be between 4.5 and 8 hours, lots of climbing and the beautiful scenery of the southern Rockies.  

http://www.nmts.org/rides/SEnchantedCircle.htm
registration: Sign-up at the El Nogal Campground, 7:30-8:00 am Sunday August 14th.  You will be required to sign a USAC waiver before you start!  $20 suggested donation.  There will also be a $5 fee for a one-day USAC cycling license if you do not have an annual license.  Makes checks payable to Velo del Norte.
directions:
Date: August 14, 2011 @ 8:15 am sharp!

Location:  El Nogal Campground, 2 miles east of Taos on Highway 64.  There is very limited parking available here, please carpool and consider parking in town and riding to the campground for sign-up.
